msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Medical compilation with a particular focus on the plague, but also including information on diseases of different parts of the body, urine, medicines, laxatives, water and wine, and the making of pigments for painting and inks for writing (f. 209r-215r).
msContents.textLang: Middle High German, with some Latin

supportDesc.extent: 326 leaves : 148 x 96 (119-124 x 75-80) mm. bound to 155 x 116 mm

collation.p: Paper, 326; 1¹⁶(-1, front pastedown) 2¹²(-1) 3¹² 4¹⁶ 5²⁰ 6¹⁶ 7¹⁴ 8¹⁰ 9-13¹⁴ 14¹⁰ 15¹⁴ 16¹⁶ 17¹¹ 18-24¹² 25⁸(-1, back pastedown); [i-xiv, 1], 2-37, 36, 38-47, 45, 48, 47, 49-52, 44, 53-255, 260-280, [i], 281-305, [306-311], contemporary foliation in ink in 2 schemes, the older in red ink upper center recto, and later in black ink, upper right recto. References in this record are to the black foliation, unless only red foliation is present.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in Gothic cursive script by multiple hands.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrication, underlining, and paragraph marks in red; initials touched with red.

binding.p: Limp parchment, a leaf from a 15th-century liturgical manuscript; paper spine.

origin.p: Written in Germany in the second half of the 15th century.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Ulricus Fugger, shelfmark XVIII K 9 (upper left, upper cover).
Sold at auction at Sotheby's, 23 June 1992, lot 67.
Sold by Les Enluminures (Paris and Chicago), Apr. 1993.
Formerly owned by John D. Stanitz (Cleveland, Ohio), Ms. 26.
Acquired by Lawrence J. Schoenberg with other Stanitz manuscripts, Sept. 1997.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2012.
